By Joe Apu FIBA Africa Zone 3 Secretariat has written to formally inform the Nigeria Basketball Federation, NBBF of its 2022 edition of the Jordan Nwora Foundation Elite Basketball Camps. The Nigeria leg of the camps which are billed to hold in three cities according to a letter signed by the President of FIBA Africa Zone 3, Col. Sam Ahmedu and addressed to the NBBF President, Ahmadu Musa Kida stated that the three cities are Lafia, Nasarawa State; Onitsha, Anambra State and Lagos. According to Col. Ahmedu, FIBA Africa Zone 3 is once again partnering with the Jordan Nwora Foundation to organize the 2022 edition of the Jordan Nwora Foundation Elite Basketball Camps in 2022.